# Usage Instructions
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Set project name:
#    - COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME (e.g., "my-project-aad")
#    - This prevents conflicts when running multiple projects
#
# 3. Fill in your authentication:
#    - CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN (Max Plan - recommended)
#    - OR ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (API users)
#
# 4. Configure Git settings:
#    - GIT_USER_NAME (default: Claude AI)
#    - GIT_USER_EMAIL (default: claude@example.com)
#
# 5. Optional: Configure GitHub CLI
#    - Set GITHUB_TOKEN for automatic gh auth
#
# 6. Optional: Configure Gemini CLI
#    - Uncomment GEMINI_API_KEY if needed
#
# 7. Build and run:
#    docker-compose up -d
#
# 8. Access orchestrator (replace PROJECT_NAME with your COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME):
#    docker exec -it PROJECT_NAME-orchestrator-1 bash
#
# 9. Access worker:
#    docker exec -it PROJECT_NAME-worker-1-1 bash

